# Plan: Add `image-text-to-text` Pipeline to Transformers.js

## Context

The Transformers.js library already has full model-level support for image-text-to-text
architectures (`AutoModelForImageTextToText`, `MODEL_FOR_IMAGE_TEXT_TO_TEXT_MAPPING_NAMES`,
`MODEL_TYPES.ImageTextToText`), covering LLaVA, Qwen2-VL, SmolVLM, Florence2, PaliGemma,
and others. However, no high-level `pipeline()` entry exists for this capability.

Users currently must manually load the model, processor, and tokenizer and wire them
together. The goal is to expose `pipeline('image-text-to-text', model_id)` so users can
pass an image + text prompt and receive generated text — mirroring how Python Transformers
exposes this task.

---

