# Plan: Add `image-text-to-text` Pipeline to Transformers.js

## Context

The Transformers.js library already has full model-level support for image-text-to-text
architectures (`AutoModelForImageTextToText`, `MODEL_FOR_IMAGE_TEXT_TO_TEXT_MAPPING_NAMES`,
`MODEL_TYPES.ImageTextToText`), covering LLaVA, Qwen2-VL, SmolVLM, Florence2, PaliGemma,
and others. However, no high-level `pipeline()` entry exists for this capability.

Users currently must manually load the model, processor, and tokenizer and wire them
together. The goal is to expose `pipeline('image-text-to-text', model_id)` so users can
pass an image + text prompt and receive generated text — mirroring how Python Transformers
exposes this task.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/pipelines.js` | **Primary target.** All changes go here (import, typedef, class, SUPPORTED_TASKS entry, JSDoc). |
| `tests/pipelines/test_pipelines_image_text_to_text.js` | **New test file** to create. |
| `tests/pipelines.test.js` | Register the new test module here (import + call). |

Read-only references used as patterns:
- `ImageToTextPipeline` (~line 1976) — image generation loop pattern
- `DocumentQuestionAnsweringPipeline` (~line 2733) — image + text input pattern
- `ZeroShotImageClassificationPipeline` (~line 2389) — processor + tokenizer combo
- Typedef block ~lines 185–220 — `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs` already covers our needs

---

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1 — Import `AutoModelForImageTextToText` in `src/pipelines.js`

In the existing import block from `./models.js` (~lines 18–44), add one line after
`AutoModelForVision2Seq`:

```js
